---
title: Scenario 13 — Completion-Counted Gate (Not Timer-Based)
---
sequenceDiagram
    participant Box as AnimatedListBox
    participant Pipeline as Pipeline
    participant A1 as Animation 1 (slide out)
    participant A2 as Animation 2 (slide in)
    participant A3 as Animation 3 (FLIP item B)
    participant Counter as _inflightCount

    Pipeline->>Box: ProcessSnapshot(Transfer)
    Box->>Box: OnBeforeAnimatedDiff()
    Box->>Box: DiffVisible → BeginExit(itemA) + Insert(itemB)

    Box->>A1: RunAnimation(slideOut)\ncts1 created
    Counter->>Counter: _inflightCount++ → 1

    Box->>A2: RunAnimation(slideIn)\ncts2 created
    Counter->>Counter: _inflightCount++ → 2

    Note over Box: For OrderChange, FLIP also uses RunAnimation
    Box->>A3: RunAnimation(FLIP itemB)\ncts3 created
    Counter->>Counter: _inflightCount++ → 3

    Note over A1,A3: All three animations running in parallel

    A2-->>Counter: Animation 2 completes\nDispatcher.UIThread.Post
    Counter->>Counter: _inflightCount-- → 2
    Note over Counter: 2 != 0, don't release gate

    A3-->>Counter: Animation 3 completes
    Counter->>Counter: _inflightCount-- → 1
    Note over Counter: 1 != 0, don't release gate

    A1-->>Counter: Animation 1 completes (slowest)
    Counter->>Counter: _inflightCount-- → 0
    Note over Counter: 0 == 0 → release gate!

    Counter->>Pipeline: OnAllAnimationsComplete\n_pipelineBusy = false
    Pipeline->>Pipeline: TryProcessNext

    Note over Box: --- CANCELLATION PATH ---
    Note over Box: If SnapAllAnimations is called mid-flight

    Box->>A1: cts1.Cancel()
    Box->>A2: cts2.Cancel()
    Box->>A3: cts3.Cancel()

    A1-->>Counter: ContinueWith fires\ncts1.IsCancellationRequested = true\nonCancelled() called\n_inflightCount-- → 2
    A2-->>Counter: ContinueWith fires\n_inflightCount-- → 1
    A3-->>Counter: ContinueWith fires\n_inflightCount-- → 0 → release gate

    Note over Counter: Gate is always released\nwhether animations complete\nnaturally or are cancelled.\nNo timer needed, no race.

    Note over Box: Key invariant:\n_inflightCount is incremented before RunAsync\nand decremented in ContinueWith (both paths)\nSo it always reaches 0 eventually
